				<p id="overview-link" style="float:right;" ><a href="http://spm-v1.dealmakerhelp.com/Default.htm" target="_blank">Overview of Sales Performance Manager</a></p>
                
                    <h2>Purpose</h2>                    
					<p>Revenue Outlook helps you to keep the team on track using metrics for the questions you care about, providing visibility into your sales business. Use Revenue Outlook when you are conducting your weekly Revenue or Forecast Calls.   </p>
        <p>Uncovering risks or vulnerabilities early is what most great sales managers want to achieve.  When you know there is a problem you can do something about it.  Surprises are bad, particularly when they mean that you suddenly miss your forecast number.</p>
        
                    <div class="more_info">
					<p>Managing your Revenue Outlook is critical to managing sales effectively. Identifying risks early removes surprises, and gives you time to act to fix the problem and secure your forecast. </p>
        
					<p>When you have poor visibility into projected sales, you generally have poorer sales results. You can help to alleviate that risk by using smart data-based forecasting measures. </p>
        <p>Traditionally, less than 50% of deals that are forecasted actually close as forecast, and that makes it hard to plan your business. </p>
        <p>Revenue Outlook is a data-driven forecasting approach, uncovering risk and enabling you to determine where you should focus.</p>
        <p>Revenue Outlook shows your team’s opportunities in Salesforce, organized by Revenue Type and Forecast Status, for a defined period.</p>
					</div>
                    <p><a href="javascript:void[0]" class="more_info_link">More...</a></p>
