                    <h2>Actions to Consider</h2>
                     <ul>
            <li>Establish and communicate a vision for the cadence of your weekly Revenue Outlook calls, making sure that everyone is clear on the agenda, the preparation required, and the normal flow of the session.</li>
            <li>At a basic level, ensure that everyone on the team understands his/her Goals by Revenue Type per Period.  This should be the easiest thing to do, but it is nevertheless essential that each of the sellers can tell what 'good' looks like before the start of any revenue cycle.</li>
           </ul>
                    <div class="more_info">
					<ul><li>Ensure that Managers and sellers are fully conversant with the rules that determine High Risk, Must Win, and Must Develop opportunities.  Ideally, there will have been some consultation prior to the configuration of Dealmaker Sales Performance Manager.</li>
            <li>It is important that everyone understands the quality of accurate data. Establish a weekly cadence whereby you can be sure that the data used in the weekly calls is accurate.  This will make the calls more efficient, and both sellers and managers will consequently spend less time massaging the forecast.</li>
        </ul>
					</div>
